USC
HERBARIUM
PLANTS OF SOUTH CAROLINA, U.S.A.

*GALAX APHYLLA* L.
Diapensiaceae

SUMTER COUNTY: Foliage shiny green; plants well past prime condition, shedding fruits; dense patch below *Kalmia latifolia*, *Cornus florida*, *Hamamelis virginiana*, *Carya tomentosa* (*Tillandsia usneoides*), *Vaccinium arboreum*, *Quercus falcata*, *Q. alba*, *Q. stellata*, *Q. rubra*, *Pinus echinata*, *Ilex opaca*, and with *Asplenium platyneuron*, on loamy sand of north-facing slope, just off trail at Poinsett State Park, about 0.4 miles southeast of main parking lot; 33.8017°N -80.5432°W; 166' elev.
John B. Nelson 25691                                      15 X 2005
University of South Carolina Herbarium (USCH)


Galax urceolata
Galax aphylla
